title: I'M HERE!
description: Back home... but not for long! Soon I'll be going to a different part of the world for a whole new set of adventures. Stay tuned!

title: Antarctica
description: Cauz why not?

title: It's On!
description: Alright, it's on! Today I packed up my bags, got to the center square in town to wave everyone goodbye, then went back home to get the right bags on the bike and then left for a 4-month long bike tour that is going to take me around Europe through more than 15 countries...

title: Dewy Tent, Missing the Kickstand, Meeting Grandparents and Some Rice!
description: So on this second day of my European Bike Tour, I wake up in a dewy tent, talk about getting a gear shed, show you around the campground a little and explain the weird hanging baskets in the shower area...

title: I Went Up Someone's Backyard!
description: So today started with a dewy tent again, so I packed everything up very quickly to ride to a sunny place where I could dry my stuff...

title: I Stayed At A German's House!
description: This day I made it across the border for the first time! But in Germany, my 4G was not working anymore for some reason... Helpless as I was, someone on the street saw me and offered me a place to stay, which I gratefully accepted. So that night I ended up at a German's house!

title: Taking Shelter From the Rain!
description: I cycled onwards towards Bremen, Germany. This day was pretty rainy...

title: Arrived in Bremen!
description: I finally arrived in my first big city in Germany! I finally started to realise that I cycled all the way to Bremen!

title: Exploring the city of Bremen!
description: I take a day off to explore the city of Bremen and do some other things. I go to an electronic store, look at some legos and buy some pants. Chinese food in the evening.

title: Random German Tractor Parade Encounter!
description: I leave the hostel in Bremen and use a Locus map to cycle to Hamburg. I encounter a random German tractor parade with weird carts with partying people in them. One guy even gave me some sweets!

title: I DID IT!!!
description: On the way I unfortunately got a flat tire and had to fix it, which reminded me of the last time I fixed a flat and struggled at the last bit to the point I had to call a bike shop. This time that wasn’t really an option so I kept on trying and trying to get the tire back into the rim and I almost gave up… but in the end I found the strength and conquered this tire!

title: City Cycling through Hamburg!
description: I rode a little bit over the center square and then made my way towards the Speicherstadt. Then I cycled onwards towards North-East towards Lübeck.

title: Cycling through Lübeck, Germany!
description: I make my way to the city of Lübeck, Germany. I fall down, cross the border of the ice in the ice age, fly my DJI Spark drone a little. Lots of rain on and off. Beautiful city and great times.

title: Almost Got Blown Off My Bike!
description: There was an autumn storm coming over so I planned to stay put for the day. I went to the reception to ask if the storm is going to be really bad. There was a weather alarm going on aswell which frightened me, but the storm didn't really come until I went to the supermarket...

title: Arrived in Rostock!
description: Road to Rostock. The storm from yesterday had a name: Sebastian. This day no rain hit me though.

title: Made it to Denmark!
description: I made it to the ferry port and got on the boat to Denmark! The 3rd country I ever cycled through! Got welcomed with another downpour though... But hey, I made it!

title: I LEFT MY WALLET AT THE SIDE OF THE ROAD!!
description: The worst nightmare of every bike tourer came true for me today: I left my wallet at the side of the road, only to realise it 20km later...

title: BEST CAMPSITE EVER!
description: Visited Møns klint which was absolutely beautiful. Made my way out of Møns klint towards the road that I already cycled through twice. Luckily, I was treated with one of the best campsites ever! And it was totally FREE!!

title: Arrived in Copenhagen!!
description: Made it to Copenhagen and to the hostel right next to Nyhavn.

title: Exploring Copenhagen by Bicycle
description: A great day exploring the beautiful city of Copenhagen, Denmark!

title: Wildcamping in Sweden!
description: Cycle out of the city of Copenhagen to Helsingør where I jumped on a ferry to Helsingborg, Sweden! I also wildcamped for the first time ever there!

title: I Got My Own Private Pool!
description: After about 2 weeks of pretty much non-stop cycling, I take a break in a beautiful house in Hjärsås, Sweden. It was quite an upgrade from my small little tent!

title: The First Hills and Puncturing my Air Matress...
description: I say goodbye to my hosts in Hjärsås, Sweden, where I stayed for a week. I started early so I could make a big distance.

title: Am I still in Sweden?!
description: Cycling along windmills and flat countryside in a province of Sweden called Halland, which really reminded me of my home country, Holland.

title: Cycling through Gothenborg!
description: Cycling through Gothenborg, seeing some cool places in the city. The landscape is changing, mountains are coming up.

title: LOADS of RAIN and PLAN CHANGES!
description: Rain. Loads of rain, all the time.

title: Made it to NORWAY!!
description: I made it to the border of Norway!! I had a wild camping camp spot, close to a lake with a nice view.

title: Do I need Winter Tires?!
description: It was dry so that was nice. Crossed the city of Halden where I climbed a fortress with a nice view. Oslo is coming closer. Gonna have to do some things about the bike, because cold weather is coming up...

title: I arrived in OSLO!!
description: Had some difficulties during the day but at sunset I finally arrived in Oslo and the view on the city was nice, but that was the last shot before I found the hostel wasn't as expected, so I didn't end the vlog and leave you guys with a little cliffhanger for the next one.

title: Everything Is So EXPENSIVE Here!!
description: First full day in Oslo. Made my way out of the awful hostel I was in and got another place to stay.

links.name: Exploring Oslo!! (A little better than yesterday!!)

title: Exploring Oslo!! (A little better than yesterday!!)
description: Second day in Oslo, Norway. Met up with a friend who lived there. Had some payment problems. Spent way too much money on tweaking a little on my bike in a bike shop. But I also got to explore some pretty cool stuff in the city.

title: I Almost Crashed My Drone!!
description: This day I left the pension in Oslo and went on my way to Bergen! This is going to be a difficult leg because I'm going to cross my first big mountain chain and the forecast was snow and cold for that place...

title: Beautiful Autumn Colors in Norway!
description: The first big climb was coming up... It was tough and also for the first time really cold, especially in the beginning where I had a very long downhill from my campsite...

title: Everything Is FROZEN!
description: Things are starting to get colder...

title: Definitely a TOUGH Day! And camping in the SNOW!
description: Woke up it was raining. Spent all morning trying to fix another flat tire. Got laughed at by the campground owner. Climbing in the rain, being soaking wet. Got to camp in the snow. This day was pretty tough...

title: Cycling in The ARCTIC!
description: The day started very cold again. Had to climb 3 huge mountains to make it to the place I had an Airbnb Apartment. Thanks to BicycleTouringPro I found a free hot shower along the way!

title: I'm READY for the SNOW!
description: Finally a rest day! Time to dry out all my equipment and prepare for the next stage, which was supposed to get even worse...

title: Worst Headwind EVER
description: Made my way out of Geilo. Had one of the worst headwinds ever and it didn't get any better. Luckily I could find shelter at some abandoned houses, where I also set up camp, after plowing through for 6 hours, and having covered only 42...

title: Made it to the BEAUTIFUL FJORDS!
description: Finally the road curved downhill and I rolled into the beautiful fjords area in Norway!

title: BEST DETOUR EVER!!
description: I wanted to take a ferry but it didn't leave until 3 hours after I left so I decided to go the other way around a fjord and I thought I would be faster... But at the end of the day I only made it to the other side of that ferry! I had no regrets, though.

title: I'M SMOKING!
description: It was raining for the whole day today. But at least it was warm. It was so warm that during an uphill my body started to smoke!

title: LAUGH ALL YOU WANT!! I Made It to Bergen!!
description: Long road to Bergen. Luckily it was sunny and warm, the night had been very cold though! At night I finally arrived in the city of Bergen.

title: One Day in BERGEN, Norway!
description: This day was a day full of exploring all the beautiful things there are to do in Bergen, Norway!

title: Roadside Ruins!
description: This vlog is the first from the leg from Bergen to Stavanger on my European Bike Tour. Followed the Eurovelo North Sea route. A nice ferry at the end of the day.

title: LOADS of BRIDGES
description: Beautiful scenery. Fjords aren't as high as before Bergen though. A lot of bridges and bodies of water.

title: Last Ferry to STAVANGER
description: This was probably gonna be the last cycling in Norway for me! Last bit of beautiful scenery in Western Norway.

title: I MET SOMEONE...
description: In Stavanger I met a guy at a Sturbucks who was very interested in my story and hosted me that night! I even went with him to a meeting about a business he was working for: 'ForEver Living'. He wanted me to do the same thing as well but I declined the offer.. It was quite an interesting experience though!

title: Some EXPLANATIONS and THE TIME I ALMOST GAVE UP
description: Took a train back to Oslo, from which the plan was to take a bus to Stockholm, Sweden. But it turned out bikes were not allowed on buses and the train was also not an option. I decided to cycle all the way to Stockholm, Sweden...

title: I'M GONNA DO IT!!!
description: I left Daniel's house, a guy I could stay with for free because of the Warmshowers app. He was a very nice guy and helped me plan my next leg to Stockholm, Sweden.

title: Racing to Stockholm! (part 1)
description: Cycling towards Stockholm. 400 km in 4 days...

title: Racing to Stockholm! (part 2)
description: Not much going on, loads of forests in Sweden.

title: WHERE DID YOU POOP??
description: Strong tailwind, finally some good distance: 134 km!! Spent the night at a campground where I had to poop at a pretty weird place...

title: Arrived in Stockholm!
description: Finally made it to Stockholm!

title: My Mom Has Arrived!
description: My mom came visit me in the city of Stockholm. I picked her up at the airport and we ate at an Argentinian restaurant there.

links.name: Going to Skansen Open Air Museum, Traditional Swedish Clothing and Houses!
WEIRDEST Place I've Ever Camped At!

title: Exploring Stockholm with my Mom!
description: Today me and my mom spent the day exploring the city of Stockholm. We went to the Gamla Stan (Old Town), Royal Palace, Storkyrkan and many more sites. In the afternoon we visited the History Museum about the Vikings, which was also very interesting, and free!

links.name: Going to Skansen Open Air Museum, Traditional Swedish Clothing and Houses!
WEIRDEST Place I've Ever Camped At!

title: Going to Skansen Open Air Museum, Traditional Swedish Clothing and Houses!
description: Today we visited the Skansen Open Air Museum, which is one of the best museums in Stockholm, Sweden. There are a lot of old buildings and people dressed the way they were in the old days.

links.name: WEIRDEST Place I've Ever Camped At!

title: WEIRDEST Place I've Ever Camped At!
description: Filled the day with some more sightseeing on my own. Went to some places my mom and I missed. The issue was that I couldn't stay at the Airbnb of last night anymore so I rode around the city trying to find a campground to stay. After no luck I decided to stand at a very interesting place...

links.name: Going to Skansen Open Air Museum, Traditional Swedish Clothing and Houses!

title: Made it to SUOMI FINLAND!!
description: I took a very early ferry to my next destination: Finland! Loads of islands along the way.

title: Little Bike Tour Around TURKU, Finland
description: The host of the Airbnb Apartment I stayed at gave me a little tour of the nearby town of Turku.

title: Finland ROCKS!!
description: On my way to Salo, where I could stay at a family member of one of my fans. Have only met amazing people here, Finland Rocks!

title: REAL FINNISH SAUNA EXPERIENCE!
description: After going to a few spots in Salo, Finland, I cycled on for about 40 km where I could stay at another family members' house of my fan. This one was very nice and the house was very unique, like it stood still in time. They also had an authentic Finnish sauna I could try out!

title: I Never Had To CAMP in Finland!
description: After saying goodbye to my great hosts, I cycled the last 90 km to the capital Helsinki. I also realised I never had to camp in Finland. There were always great people to host me.

title: An Epic Day in HELSINKI!
description: Today I explored the city of Helsinki! I went to a few cool places, like Suomen Linna fortress, a church in a rock and more...

title: BEAUTIFUL TALLINN
description: I went on a ferry to the next country and the next capital: Tallinn!! Tallin is a beautiful city with a lot of cool old buildings and a beautiful city center. When I first entered the city through it's Northern gate, I was very surprised.

links.name: Last Full Day in Tallinn! Last Thoughts About Forever Living

title: Some Sightseeing In Tallinn, Estonia!
description: I did some sightseeing in the city of Tallinn. Went to the Alexander Nevski Cathedral and a few viewpoints. Tallinn is one of the most beautiful cities I've ever visited.

links.name: Last Full Day in Tallinn! Last Thoughts About Forever Living

title: Last Full Day in Tallinn! Last Thoughts About Forever Living
description: Today I prepared for the next and last leg of the first part of the European Bike tour. I tried to find some new tires, but gave up because I couldn't find a bike shop that was open or at the same spot Google Maps told me it was supposed to be. Did some more sightseeing.

title: MY TIRE EXPLODED
description: Left the hostel southbound towards Latvia. About 20km out of town I heard a loud bang and had a flat tire. Later I found out there was an inch-wide hole in the outer tire, unfixable for that moment so I took a train back to Tallinn and went to the one bike shop in Tallinn I hadn't been to, turned out they had the right tires!

links.name: Last Full Day in Tallinn! Last Thoughts About Forever Living

title: I'M WIPED
description: Take 2 of my attempty to cycle to Riga, Latvia. Now with some good tires. But I pushed the boundaries quite high by booking an Airbnb apartment in Pärnu, Estonia, some 140 km away from Tallinn! I made it, but I was wiped by the end of the day.

title: Made it to LATVIA!
description: Left the quaint place in Pärnu, Estonia and made my way south towards Latvia. Had the winter sun in my face so it was pretty tough but eventually I made it to the border!

title: LAST DAY OF CYCLING!
description: The last bit of cycling for this trip was here! I decided to call it quite in Riga, Latvia for now, I will return to Riga in May 2018.

title: NATIONAL DAY IN RIGA, LATVIA
description: Coincidentally it was Latvia Independence Day right when I was there! So I went and celebrated the National Day of a country I barely knew something about. It was quite interesting.

title: LOTS OF BUSES!!
description: Luckily there was place for my bicycle on the bus to Vilnius. From there I took a nightly bus to Warsaw, where I arrived at 6 AM the next morning.

title: Exploring Warsaw, Poland!
description: I arrived at 6 AM in Warsaw. Stayed at another Airbnb and the host was very nice. We went to the Copernicus museum which wasn't so excited for us... Then we went to a couple more places which were very nice.

links.name: Visiting the Polish War Uprising Museum!

title: Visiting the Polish War Uprising Museum!
description: Today I went to some more sights in Warsaw, Poland. One of which was the Polish Uprising Museum, which was quite impressive.

title: I RECOGNIZE THIS!
description: Took a train from Warsaw, to Hannover. Due to some problems I had a layover in the city of Magdeburg, where I had been a few years ago.

title: THE LAST SIGHTSEEING PLACE!
description: Felt good to be back in Germany! Explored the city of Hanover for a little bit and realised this was gonna be the last place to sightsee on this line.

title: BACK HOME
description: My friend picked me up in Hanover and together we drove back to my home town: Rijnsburg. The trip is over, but next year I'm gonna be back at it again!

title: Saying Goodbye and The Road to BERLIN!
description: Finally European Bike Tour part 2 is starting! The plan is to slowly get back to Riga, to pick up the bike and start cycling again.

title: Exploring Berlin, Walking Along Berlin Wall and More!
description: In this vlog I start exploring the city of Berlin. I first went to Alexander Platz. Compared West-Berlin with East-Berlin and that the differences are very noticeable. Walked to East-Side Gallery where parts of the original wall were still standing.

links.name: Another Impressive Day in Berlin! Checkpoint Charlie, Potsdamer Platz, Memorial to the Murdered Jews

title: Another Impressive Day in Berlin! Checkpoint Charlie, Potsdamer Platz, Memorial to the Murdered Jews
description: On this second day in Berlin I visit Checkpoint Charlie, and start walking along the wall border again. I past Potsdamer Platz, told some history about it, went to the Memorial to the Murdered Jews in Europe and walked until I came back to the place I was yesterday.

links.name: Exploring Berlin, Walking Along Berlin Wall and More!

title: Can't Believe I Made It Onto That Bus!
description: A full day of bustravel from Berlin to Vilnius! And a lot more eventful than I expected...

title: I Ate PIG'S EARS?!
description: In this vlog I finally arrive in Vilnius, Lithuania! I looked around the city a bit, settled in my Airbnb room and ate out with a fan of the channel who got me some very interesting dinner...

links.name: Visiting Trakai Island Castle (Trakų Salos Pilis)!

title: Visiting Trakai Island Castle (Trakų Salos Pilis)!
description: In this episode I visit Trakai Castle about 1 hour outside of Vilnius. The castle is a beautiful orange Lithuanian castle, that originates from the Middle Ages. I rented a bike and rode around the area as well!

title: Free Walking Tour Through Vilnius!
description: In this vlog I joined a free walking tour through Vilnius, which was very nice. The organization is called Vilnius With Locals (www.vilniuswithlocals.com) and the tour was about 2.5 hours. We walked past all the main highlights and heard a lot about the history of the city.

links.name: Visiting Trakai Island Castle (Trakų Salos Pilis)!

title: A Very Interesting Hostel..
description: On the road from Vilnius to Riga, where I will start my tour again! In Riga I had booked a very interesting hostel...

title: Reunited With My Bike!!
description: Start the day with the news that I might not be cycling alone for the first couple of days. Then picking up the bike. We are reunited again!

title: First Day Of Cycling!!
description: So today the cycling officially began! It was a relaxed day because Sofie likes to sleep in and wanted to leave at around noon, which was ok for me because I still had to do laundry (which didn't happen unfortunately) and afterwards I went to Sofie's hostel and together we rode out of the city of Riga towards the coast.

title: Reaching the Northernmost Point for the Trip!
description: So today we woke up on our incredible location along the beach. Probably the best campsite I've ever stayed at. Sofie is not so much of a morning person, so I had some time while she was still sleeping to explore the coast a little bit. We reached Kolka, the tip of Latvia, which meant that it is all south from here for me!

title: I've Got 42 Mosquito Bites!!
description: We rode southwards through beautiful nature. The water filter came in handy because there were no places with clean drinking water. Sofie had to buy bottled water. Headwinds.. At camp, I counted my mosquito bites, I had 42 of them!! Oh, and Sofie had ZERO!

title: WRONG ROAD!!
description: We started the day at our campsite in Ventspils. Then we cycled out of town, but stumbled across a road that would turn into dirt, which was indicated by a sign. We turned around, which was the better choice!

title: Made It To Lithuania!!
description: Rainstorm last night. New kickstand for Sofie. Came across the first recumbent cyclist I've seen so far. A lot of storks. Found a bike shop in Liepaja, Latvia. Cycled across the border into Lithuania! Country nr. 9!! Dirt road to our beautiful campsite in Sventoji, Lithuania.

title: Only Cycling Paths!! Cycling On The Curonian Spit!
description: Cycling on cycle paths pretty much all the way. Reminds me of home, also because of the landscape having a lot of dunes. Passed the town of Klaipeda, where we took a ferry to ride on the Curonian Spit, all the way to Nida!

title: Walking On Dunes on The Curonian Spit! And Saying Goodbye To Sofie
description: Full day in Nida. Sofie and I took a look at the Russian border, climbed some sandy dunes and eventually we said goodbye to each other and Sofie took the ferry to the mainland.

links.title: Another video from the Curonian Spit:

links.name: Flying The Drone Over The Curonian Spit!

title: Lots of Rain, Drone Flying and How to Clean Yourself While Wild Camping!
description: Started the day in heavy rain. Got a ferry to the mainland of Lithuania and started cycling eastwards. Flew the drone and showed how to clean yourself while wildcamping.

title: Getting Some Fuel and Germans Everywhere!
description: Had a good night sleep in the forest. Went to a gas station to fill up my fuel bottle for my campstove, which I've never done before! Only had to pay 72 cents for it. Lunch in Jurbarkas, Lithuania. Thought it was a local place, but ended up meeting 3 other German bicycle tourists at this place! Cycled to a campground which turned out to be really good.

title: I Accidentally Treated Myself!
description: Cycling to Kaunas. It is pretty cold, almost feels like autumn! But soon will be better again. A hungry climb towards a supermarket. Bought a bit too much. Made it to Kaunas and to my own airbnb apartment! I didn't know I was gonna have an entire apartment for myself. So I accidentally treated myself to an entire apartment for 3 nights.

title: Beautiful Kaunas!
description: Today I went out to explore the city of Kaunas. The second biggest town of Lithuania. I went to St. Michael the Archangel's Church, Kaunas Cathedral Basilica and Kaunas Castle. Also ventured out of the center up the hill and then back down towards the castle, from which I went back to the apartment to do some work.

title: Hot Weather and Dirt Roads means Sweat!
description: hecking out of my Airbnb apartment. Riding out of Kaunas. Construction on cycle lanes. No direct route to Poland so taking the backroads is best, but not guaranteed to be paved so I had some dirt roads and it was hot, so I was very sweaty.

title: Hello Poland!
description: Very late start today. I met up with a Swiss guy called Jan yesterday and showed him in the vlog a bit. He is motorbiking around Northern Europe. I have to edit a video with a deadline, which takes up all morning and a bit of the afternoon. I leave camp at 2 PM and head south. Made a choice to not follow the main highway to Poland but instead take a side road. Found a WWII bunker at the side of the road and decided to take a look.

title: Following The Green Velo Route in Poland!
description: First full day of cycling in Poland. Packed up at my wild camping place and headed to a place called Augustow to do some website work that had a deadline. Then I went on to cycling in the afternoon and encountered the Green Velo route in Poland, which was very well laid out and had rest stops along it.

title: Beard Or No Beard?
description: Rain in the morning, cold weather. Following the Green Velo Route again. Found a place to warm up and charge my items and eat some Polish soup. Found a free place to stay again. Cold cooking, talking about the financial situation and that I can't keep this train rolling for much longer.. as well as you guys decide what I should do with the beard. Beard or no beard, you decide!

title: I'm So Done!!!
description: Start riding in the rain.. my plans changed because of the weather. I decided to take a break a bit early, instead of cycling for another 2 days. I rented another airbnb in Bialystok which was definitely the right choice because the weather for the next days were horrible.

title: Sorry, I Don't Speak Polish..
description: Talk about Esperanto in Bialystok, then ride out towards the east, to Bialowieza forest.

title: Sometimes You Gotta Be Flexible...
description: Josef from TheOneGoodRoad called me this morning and we talked for 2.5 hours, which threw my plans for the day a little off-guard. Unfortunately my plans fell completely through when I came across a sign which said that the road to the Primieval forest (Bialowieza) was closed. It forced me to ride around the forest..

title: Droning Around Ancient Ruins In Poland!!
description: Check out of hotel, make my way south. Unfortunately skipping the Bialowieza forest for now. Some nice dirt roads first, but they turned into bad sandy ones later. Showcasing my staple foods for lunch, talking about going to a Sklep, but there was no one around. Diverge from Green velo for a bit to avoid the dirt roads.

title: MY FIRST CENTURY!!
description: When I was waiting for a ferry that didn't go, I realised I made a mistake... To rectify I wanted today to be the longest ever and ended up cycling my first 100 miles on 1 day! I was completely shattered by the end of the day and allowed myself to have a little hotel.

title: That Is Ukraine!
description: Cycling along the Poland-Ukraine border. Nice encounter with a truck. Dji Spark drone flying. Crossed the town of Sobibor, where one of the extermination nazi camps were located. Past the highway bordercrossing, but I'll cross into Ukraine tomorrow. I did see Ukraine today, across the river. Went to a Polish Sklep, where I left the cassier very confused because of the language barrier. Sometimes you gotta make a fool of yourself.

title: I'M IN UKRAINE!!
description: Crossed the border to Ukraine! First time cycling across a guarded border. Cycled to a town called Chervonohrad where I had a motel for 13 euros a night. Tomorrow ride to a town called Lviv, where I will take a little break for a few days.

title: Crazy Steep Hills and Bad Roads in Ukraine!
description: Cycling Ukraine is very different from the rest of Europe. Highway is kind of dangerous, found some tracks of trucks going into the shoulder. Diverged from the highway, to some backroads, which was a bad idea, because the hills became very steep and the roads very bad. I had to push my bike up some very steep hills to the point I was covered in sweat.

title: Rainy Lviv!!
description: Today I explored rainy Lviv in Ukraine while I was there for 5 days. The first few days I was inside working and as soon as I wanted to get out and explore the city, it started pooring down! I went to the city center, after which I made my way to the Park Lviv High Castle to see a nice view of the city.

title: I'm The Master Rain Avoider!!!
description: Cycle out of Lviv in the rain, a lot of rain and thunder so I wanted to take a train in the direction that I'm going, unfortunately that was not an option. So I cycled, it became dryer, but there were a lot of dark clouds around me all the time. Cycled to a place called Sambir, stayed there in a really cheap hotel with a very nice owner.

title: Camping On Top Of A Mountain!
description: Cycling from Sambir, Ukraine into the Carpathian mountains.Talking about my experience yesterday with going to a Ukrainian church with my hotel host, Igor. Then I said goodbye and cycled into the rain. Dji Spark drone flying. Couldn't find a place to stay in a town, so i decided to camp in the wild. First place got scared away by dogs of herders, then I found a beautiful spot on top of a mountain.

title: Cycling Through The Carpathian Mountains In Ukraine!
description: Woke up on top of Mount. Ostra in Ukraine. Cycling through foggy Carpathian Mountains in Ukraine. First part was very hilly but after I passed a military checkpoint the road became worse but it was only downhill. I made it to a place called Uzhhorod where I booked a hostel for 4 euros a night.

title: Bye Ukraine, Hello Slovakia!!
description: Crossed the border into Slovakia. Had an interesting hostel experience, Hrishna meditators came to the hostel to meditate. Back in the EU, Slovakia uses the euros, prices are a bit more expensive. Dji Spark drone flying. Steep hill on the way to Kosice, which was the end destination for the day. My apartment is at Sandor Marai's place, a popular Hungarian writer.

title: Practice Cooking And Feeling A Bit Lonely...
description: Full day in Kosice, did some sightseeing because I needed to find a cafe with wifi, because the wifi at my airbnb place really sucked. Practiced some cooking and at the end of the day I felt a bit down.. I hadn't met many people there and felt a bit lonely..

title: Meeting People In Krakow! - Couchsurfing Experience
description: Leaving Kosice by bus. Arriving in Krakow, I felt a bit lonely in Kosice and wanted to make an effort to meet people in Krakow. So I went on Couchsurfing and found people who wanted to hangout with me. I hung out with a French teacher in Lithuania, and afterwards went to a Couchsurfing meetup in the city. I completely forgot to film that, but it was a lot of fun and I got a little tipsy...

links.title: A playlist to all videos I did during my stay in Krakow:

title: Climbing My First Mountain In the Tatra Mountains!
description: Early train to Zakopane. Start hiking from Kuznice, into the Tatra mountains towards a mountain called Koscielec. I climbed this 2155 m mountain with some tough terrain at the end. Spectacular views, unfortunately no DJI drone flying..

title: Meeting BicycleTouringPro In Poznan, Poland!
description: Today I met Darren Alff from  BicycleTouringPro, the man who made bicycle touring popular. It was very interesting to meet up with him and ride around Poznan together. We had Indian Curry for lunch and then we went for another round around Poznan. Afterwards I went back to my apartment to have some sushi.

title: I Don't Like Buses!
description: Bus from Poznan to Krakow.

title: Climbing My First Mountain In the Tatra Mountains!
description: Early train to Zakopane. Start hiking from Kuznice, into the Tatra mountains towards a mountain called Koscielec. I climbed this 2155 m mountain with some tough terrain at the end. Spectacular views, unfortunately no DJI drone flying..

title: Desert In Poland?!! Exploring Lesser Poland with a Local, Błędów Desert, Park Gródek and More!
description: Left Krakow today, went to a small place in Lesser Poland called Krzykawa. In this place a fan of the channel lives, who really wanted to hosted me and showed me around the area. We went to Błędów Desert, Park Gródek in Jaworzno and explored a lot in this beautiful region between Katowice and Krakow and shot some beautiful DJI Spark drone shots.

links.title: The 2nd day of my stay at Zbigniew:

links.name: Visiting Amazing Polish Castles And A Cave + Gear Update!

title: Back In The Saddle Again!
description: Today saying goodbye to Zbigniew, back in the saddle again. Going to the Czech Republic. Today was just Poland. Camping at a campground and cooking some soup and dumplings.

title: Crossed Into Czechia!!
description: Today I made it to my last new European country: The Czech Republic. Told about my future plans and about Australia. Made it to the town of Ostrava where I got a room in a pension for 2 nights. For the last days of cycling to Prague I didn't want to spend any money on a place to stay.

title: My First Night Couchsurfing!!
description: Have a challenge to not spend on places to sleep until Prague. Hilly cycling, met Pavel that traveled for 2 weeks without any money. Arrived in Olomouc where I luckily was able to be hosted by a couchsurfer. It's gonna be a short night because I had to get up at 5 AM!

title: Cooking Some Nice Meals While Wild Camping In The Czechian Woods!
description: Early start this morning because of my couchsurfing host having to go to work. Very tired, taking a lot of breaks. Hilly riding. Found a beer factory. At night wild camping and making some nice dishes. An omelette and afterwards spicy peanut butter pasta from the Bike camp cook book. I also show how to clean your dishes while wild camping.

title: Trying To Make Some Pancakes While Wild Camping!
description: Woke up at my wild camping place, well rested. Cycling through some more hilly terrain again. Sparsely populated area in Czechia I was cycling through, a lot of old houses, small villages. Another wild camping place in the night. Making some pancakes, learning more to become a camp cook. They didn't come out perfectly and I burnt myself a bit, but I learnt and I can move on.

title: Last Day Of Cycling For A While...
description: Omelette for breakfast, long cycling day to Prague. A very hot day as well so I rewarded myself multiple times with good food. Have a little talk about my trip so far and that it has been another amazing experience. Made it to my Airbnb place at night. Very tired.
A lot happened in Prague. I explored the city, made some friends and went beyond my comfort zone. In this video I explain what happened in Prague.
